x4freetext: 4 MV VAN DE GRAAFF.
LI-F TARGET, DEPOSITED BY EVAPORATION UNDER
VACUUM ONTO A TA-BACKING OF 0.5 MM THICKNESS.
THIS TARGET IS WATER COOLED. THE CURRENT CAN BE
50 MICRO-AMPERES.
.THE NEUTRON RESOLUTION STEMS FROM
- THE PROTON RESOLUTION (NEGLIGIBLE)
- ENERGY LOSSES IN THE TARGET 2.5(FOR 1.5 MICRO-
GRAMS/CM**2)-10.KEV(FOR 75 MICRO-GRAMS/CM**2)
- ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION OF THE (P,N) REACTION.
.DATA TAKEN FROM THESIS OF BARREAU.
G.C.
.PREPARED BY THE NUCLEAR CHEMISTRY SERVICE OF THE
CEN-BORDEAUX, BY ELECTROPLATING ON A NI-BACKING
OF 10 MICRONS THICK. IT HAS A USEFUL DIAMETER OF
2 CM AND A THICKNESS OF 0.8 MG/CM**2. ITS ISOTOPIC
COMPOSITION WAS 99.68 PERCENT U-234, 0.062 PERCENT
U-235, 0.01 PERCENT U-236 AND 1.6E-04 PERCENT U-238.
.MEASUREMENT OF THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION WITH
A TRACK DETECTOR. THE TARGET WAS ROTATING DURING
THE MEASUREMENT AS TO ELIMINATE ARTIFICIAL
ANISOTROPIES DUE TO THE INHOMOGENITIES OF
SOURCE AND/OR NEUTRON BEAM. THE DISTORTION OF
THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS BY THE FINITE GEOMETRY
WAS CALCULATED IN A MONTE CARLO SIMULATION AND
PROVED TO BE SMALL FOR A RADIUS OF THE TRACK
DETECTOR OF 9 CM. THE DETECTION EFFICIENCY OF
THE DETECTOR WAS DETERMINED WITH A CF-252
SOURCE.
MACROFOL K.G. OF CYLINDRICAL SHAPE
WITH A RADIUS OF 9. CM.
.DATA TAKEN FROM TABLE ON P.97 OF THESIS OF BARREAU.
G.C.

CEN-BORDEAUX, BY ELECTROPLATING ON A NI-BACKING
OF 10 MICRONS THICK. IT HAS A USEFUL DIAMETER OF

.MEASUREMENT OF THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION WITH
A TRACK DETECTOR. NO FURTHER DETAILS.
TWO DISKS OF MACROFOL OF 10 MICRONS
THICKNESS. SOLID ANGLES ABOUT 5 STERRADIANS.
THESE FOILS ARE PLACED IN AN ALUMINIUM BOX
WITH A DIAMETER OF 8 CM AND A HEIGHT OF 5 CM.
TWO BACK-TO-BACK FOILS OF U-234 ARE PLACED IN
THE CENTRE OF THIS CHAMBER.
.DATA TAKEN FROM TABLE 3.4, P.173 OF THESIS.
G.C.
